measurements.description:
Thirty-two flowers and 69 buds on 14 up to 4.2-cm inflorescences; 
 borne on a scandent, rhizomatous, leafless plant; inflorescences arising from the junction between rhizome and roots;  
 dorsal sepal erect, widely elliptic, acute, yellow-brown;
 lateral sepals slightly reflexed, widely elliptic, acute, yellow-brown;
 petals minute, triangular, light green-brown;
 lip white, midlobe obcordate, spur 0.5 cm in length, yellow-brown; 
 column erect, orange, anther cap orange;

 substance thin; texture matte; awarded as an unusal species for North American culture; general appearance mostly roots;
 an interesting example of a leafless orchid.
